entries.title: US shoots down Chinese 'spy balloon' off Carolina coast
entries.description: The US has shot down a suspected Chinese spy balloon that has been flying over its airspace.

entries.title: 'Significant' accident at electricity substation in Ukraine leaves half a million without power
entries.description: Half a million people have been left without power after a "significant" accident at an electricity substation in Odesa, southern Ukraine.

entries.title: Chinese 'spy balloon' spotted again in US airspace
entries.description: A suspected Chinese spy balloon has been spotted again in US airspace - this time over North Carolina.

entries.title: Shark kills 16-year-old girl after she jumped from jet ski into water
entries.description: A teenage girl has been killed in a shark attack in Australia.

entries.title: Bodies of British volunteers killed in Ukraine returned in prisoner swap with Russia
entries.description: The bodies of two British volunteers have been returned following a prisoner swap with Russia, Ukraine has announced.

entries.title: 'It's painful': US facing record-breaking wind chill factors so cold they're literally off the charts
entries.description: Parts of the US are experiencing a record-breaking wind chill factor that is so cold it's literally off the National Weather Service's official charts.

entries.title: The puzzling theories behind China's 'spy balloons' - and why none bode well for US relations
entries.description: There is much about the Chinese spy balloon story that is genuinely puzzling.

entries.title: China denies US spy balloon claims and insists it always 'abides by international law'
entries.description: China has claimed the flight of an "airship" over the US was an accident and accused politicians and media of taking advantage of the situation.
